summary: This ENB preset is very un-realistic but quite moody, dark and fantasy-like. Compatible with ENB version .168.
descriptionHtml:
[center][img]http://imageshack.us/a/img32/3610/3knw.jpg[/img]
				
JT ENB version 1.14 release
ONLY COMPATIBLE WITH ENB V0.168[/center]



[center]-----------------------------[/center]
[IMG]http://imageshack.us/a/img545/5066/enb2013517173127.jpg[/IMG]


I\'m far from being a programmer or a professional at things like this.
This preset can have graphical artifacts and some bugs, and to a seasoned ENB proffessional
this preset will likely look like utter shite lol. 
I will try my best to get rid of these bugs if and when I find any. But if it works
on my monitor, then I\'m happy. :P


[youtube]3XqRPQXR-h0[/youtube]
[center]-----------------------------[/center]


This preset comes in 3 versions: 

Default 	(the ...well... default one)
Performance	(a faster version with most effects disabled and their quality reduced, FPS is set to 32 to limit stuttering)
Heavy Duty	(if your PC can hold 60 FPS with this version I\'m either impressed or you need to return your PC to NASA... Suited for screenshots.)

There are also optional files if you like no grain or less grain, no black bars/vignette and anamorphic flare.

[center]-----------------------------[/center]

Installing:

1.	First download the ENB binary .dll file. These files are forbidden to be uploaded to Nexus.
	http://www.enbdev.com/download_mod_tesskyrim.htm is the adress. Go ahead and download v0.168. 
	Pace it in The Elder Scrolls V Skyrim root folder (where TESV.exe is located)

2.	Go to Documents\\My Games\\Skyrim, open your skyrimprefs.ini, under [Display] add or modify the following line: bFloatPointRenderTarget=1
	Also check the following lines: bDrawShadows=1  bDrawLandShadows=1

3.	Open one of the three folders (JT ENB Default, JT ENB Performance or JT ENB Heavy Duty), copy EVERYTHING here, 
	paste in The Elder Scrolls V Skyrim root folder (where TESV.exe is located).
	Overwrite when asked. 

4.	Play Skyrim
	

Uninstalling:

1. Remove all the included files. Or you can use the uninstaller which can be found in \"Files\" section as miscellaneous. 
[img]http://imageshack.us/a/img89/2005/enb201356171925i.jpg[/img]

[center]-----------------------------[/center]
There are also 5 additional mods that comes with this preset. They are loaded according to the following list:
FixedEyeAdaption.esp          -Made by GSJ1977 
enbweather.esp          -Made by --JawZ--
ENB Weather - Exterior Fog Plugin.esp         -Made by --JawZ--
RevampedExteriorFog.esp          -Made by Gargorias
Dark Dungeons for ENB         -Made by Mindflux/Artem1s

If you have a lot of mods I suggest BOSS mod, or Better Oblivion Sorting Software. This program sets the correct load order for all your mods. 
Go to: http://code.google.com/p/better-oblivion-sorting-software/downloads/list


[img]http://imageshack.us/a/img690/4059/9ay6.jpg[/img]
